SIMPLE: scarifier
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scarifier
<hw>Scar"i*fi`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who scarifies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>The instrument used for
scarifying.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Agric.)</fld> <def>An implement for stripping and
loosening the soil, without bringing up a fresh surface.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You have your <qex>scarifiers</qex> to make the ground clean.</q>
<rj><qau>Southey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scarify</ent>⟦br⟧
